				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just recently started a mage, he's 31, and lately I have been trying to figgure a way to pull singles with the pet. I parked the pet close enough to a group of mobs that when told, the pet would attack. I would then back way out of agro range, tell the pet to attack, wait for it to agro the mob then use pet back off and follow me to get a single. I had some luck overall but it wasn't 100% reliable. 
<br />

<br />
Hopefully you all will be able to tell me the specifics of this kind of pull. Thanks in advance for any information you might have on the subject.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
