			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Pet pulling is a great technique -- congrats on the resourcefullness to find it so early!
<br />

<br />
There are a few things to keep in mind when you use it. 
<br />

<br />
Your pet is neutral to all until it gets on a mob's hate list. It can do that by melee, casting, or taunting a mob. As soon as it is on the hate list of the mob, it then is subject to "social aggro" from nearby mobs.
<br />

<br />
Your pet is lower level than you are. Aggro radius, both normal and social, seem to increase with lower levels. You may be a better choice as a puller than your pet in some situations because of this.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">/pet hold </span>(Pet Discipline) AA makes this much easier, as you don't have to spam <span style="font-style: italic">/pet back off </span>or pound on the UI button (easier). Then again, you need to be in your 50s to get that AA.
<br />

<br />
Summoning mobs make this more difficult, but not impossible. It just takes Jobober longer to get back if being chain summoned. 
<br />

<br />
Equipping/buffing your pet helps to reduce the chance that your pet is beaten to a pulp before it gets back to you.
<br />

<br />
Simply sending your pet in makes the mob angry at you. Don't be surprised if you are cast upon. Expect that somehow the mob knows <span style="font-style: italic">exactly </span>which slot KEI is in when it dispells you. Every time...
<br />

<br />
You can pet pull and split. Two mobs incoming on your pet, make sure your tagger knows which is which. Tagger range-attacks one, you sic your pet on the other. (You can be both -- check the Options menu and define the toggle-to-last-target key.) <span style="font-style: italic">/pet hold </span>pretty much required for reliability on this since you don't want any more than the barest amount of aggro on the mob that will be tagged.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
