<br />

<br />
Ok. There's a tighly grouped bunch of mobs that you want one out of .
<br />

<br />
You park Goner   <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /> just close enough so that when you tell him he attacks and when you send him in you back off as far as you can safely get.
<br />

<br />
If you're far enough away you wont get any adds.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">BUT</span> you actually do have agro on those surrounding mobs and the next time you get close enough they'll attack.
<br />

<br />
Does that make any sense, that you have agro but you're out of their range for them to attack you ? Cause thats the way it seems to work for me.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
