			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I honestly don't know about the aggro. I generally don't bind in the zone where I am fighting for a lot of reasons.
<br />

<br />
About the pet -- certainly anything that brings up LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... removes even suspended pets (e.g., Evac, Succor).
<br />

<br />
I was surprised when I just cast a pet on my bind point and gated to find the pet still there. I do know that if a pet can't find its way back to you, it will soon poof. I have seen this in Velks as well as places like BoT towers. Clicking your Silverflank Belt, or other Summon Companion method quickly can resolve this.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like something worth checking. You can /assist the mob to see who is at the top of its hate list.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
